race.comment: Very even race. Staying with DON'T STOP ME NOW (13) who broke through for an overdue maiden win last time out at Esk with a kill over 1460m. Returns home and very attractively weighted with the claim. At top and confidence up can make it two on end. EXTOL (7) is building to a win and went close latest when runner-up here last time. Placed 2/2 this course and distance and can break through. TICKLE MY TOSEN (9) has been a bit plain in two runs back but now gets out in journey and strips fitter. Expected to improve sharply. DEL TITO (17) turned in a nice return over 1400m after a long lay-off. Far fitter for it and looks a leading player. MUCHACHO (6) was a winner two back then below best last time in a strong form race on the Gold Coast. Better than that and will take catching here.
